{
    "name": "Argorth",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The horrifying, incomprehensible spawn of the Mothers of Oblivion, these titans of destruction are weaned on bloodshed and the dark dreams of Lamashtu herself. Nearly 30 feet tall, these marauding tentacles know only rage and slaughter, laying waste to whole regions, paving the way for their dark mistresses\u2019 hordes of ravening monsters. Unnatural disasters, argorths have more in common with hurricanes and volcanos than the beasts of the natural world."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<img src=\"images\\ThreeFiveSymbol.gif\" style=\"margin: 3px 3px 0px 3px\"/><i>An avalanche of gnashing teeth, bone hooks, and worm coils roils forward in a wave of sundering parts. At the forefront of this thrashing, tentacular body yawns a howling pit of a mouth, ringed with a spiral of churning teeth and three massive, spiked mandibles.</i>",
